sentences: Iren Dimitrova (Bulgarian: Ирен Димитрова) (born 1950) is a Bulgarian piano player and tutor of piano accompaniment and chamber music.

She enjoyed a long performance and teaching career, and taught chamber music and piano accompaniment in the National Art School of Varna, piano at the Varna Free University "Chernorizets Hrabar", at the University of Shumen "Constantine of Preslav" and the Higher Institute of Music of Sfax.
In 2011 she was honoured with the Lifetime Achievement Award.
